# Convex client contract

## Mutation args must match what clients send

Before marking a field required in a mutation, check **all** callers (native, web, admin). If any client conditionally omits a value, the arg must be optional:

```ts
// Schema already optional — mutation must match
imageId: v.optional(v.id("_storage")),

// Handler: resolve storage only when present
let imageUrl: string | undefined;
if (args.imageId) {
  imageUrl = (await ctx.storage.getUrl(args.imageId)) ?? undefined;
  if (!imageUrl) throw new ConvexError({ code: "INVALID_ARGUMENT", message: "..." });
}
```

Rule: read `schema.ts` first. Required mutation args that aren't required in the table definition will cause runtime validation errors when clients pass `undefined`.

## Cross-app grep before tightening args

When changing journal/entry mutations, grep:

- `apps/native/**`
- `apps/web/**`
- `apps/admin/**`
- `packages/backend/convex/**`

Do not require `imageId`, `coverImageId`, or `audioId` unless every caller always provides them.
